      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mid-range operating point hemolysis validation (3.5 L/min, 3000 RPM)",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 3.5 L/min and 3000 RPM. Predicted NIH = 0.0041 g/100 L versus measured NIH = 0.0044 ± 0.0006 g/100 L. Relative error 6.8%, within acceptance band. This single operating point lies in the mid-range of the COU envelope and is consistent with the linear scalar stress–exposure precondition of the Giersiepen–Wurzinger model.",
      "validationMetric": "Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH)",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "comparisonError": 0.068
